    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but the \"non-local\" part is what's tripping me up. Einstein famously called it \"spooky action at a distance.\" Why did he call it spooky? Like, what is it about the way they interact that feels so weird or counterintuitive compared to normal physics?",
